</md></sn><sn><md>### Distance from the Sea{.text-center}

* The main factor influencing temperature is the position of a place with respect to the sea.
* The `sea` heats up and cools down `slowly`, while `land` heats up and cools down `rapidly`.
* Hence, temperature variation over the `sea is less compared to land`.
* Coastal places experience the moderating influence of sea and land breezes, which regulate temperature.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Air-Mass and Ocean Currents{.text-center}

* The passage of air masses affects temperature in a similar way as sea and land breezes.
* Areas influenced by `warm air` masses experience `higher temperatures`, while those affected by `cold air` masses experience `lower temperatures`.
* Coastal regions with warm ocean currents record higher temperatures than those with cold currents.

